== John Reid's Course of Practical Alchemy
_by John Reid III, Second Edition (1993). Magnum Opus, Inc._

#hm-note[
  John Reid III is a self-taught practitioner who, working largely through divine revelation and persistent laboratory experience, produced the clearest English-language account of the transition from spagyric to alchemical plant work available in the modern era.\
  
  His unique contribution is the complete Minor Opus (Plant Stone) protocol taken through all colour stages with photographic documentation, and his distinction between "spagyric" and "alchemical" products — the former separating what nature has already manifested, the latter generating the spark of life itself by art.\

  Reid's Three Essentials doctrine diverges significantly from Albertus and Junius: ethyl alcohol, volatile oil, and mineral salts are *vehicles* of the essentials, not the essentials themselves.\
  
  The essentials proper are the two celestial waters — the condensed starlight (Sulfur/male) and the collected precipitation (Salt/female) — whose preparation is the subject of Chapter 8.\
  
  In the TTAO curriculum, Reid is the primary authority for the Water Work and sealed-vessel fermentation (Year 2), and the Minor Opus photographic sequence (Chapters 9 and Conclusion) is the definitive visual reference for the colour progression of the Plant Stone.
]
